4. PROHIBITED DISTRIBUTIONS AND PENALTIES
================================================================================

4.1 Prohibition. You may not create, publish, or maintain any Prohibited
Distribution. Doing so constitutes a material breach of this license and
violation of the copyright holder's rights.

4.2 Consequences of breach.

  (a) All rights granted under this license terminate automatically, worldwide,
      as to you and any entity you control or that distributes the Prohibited
      Distribution with your knowledge or participation.

  (b) You agree that actual damages for a Prohibited Distribution are difficult
      to ascertain and that the following amounts are reasonable estimates of
      harm and not penalties: (i) liquidated damages of fifty thousand United
      States dollars (USD 50,000) per distinct Prohibited Distribution (e.g.,
      per app store listing or per distinct product), and (ii) an additional
      fifty thousand United States dollars (USD 50,000) if the Prohibited
      Distribution is malicious or cognitively abusive as described in
      Section 1(c). The copyright holder may seek these amounts in addition to
      any other remedies.

  (c) The copyright holder is entitled to seek injunctive relief (including
      removal of listings and cessation of distribution) without proof of
      monetary harm.

  (d) In any action to enforce this license or redress a Prohibited
      Distribution, the prevailing party may recover reasonable attorneys'
      fees and costs from the non-prevailing party.

4.3 The remedies in this Section 4 are cumulative and not exclusive of any
other remedies at law or in equity.

